---
// Closed-Loop Self-Dosing — protein → hearing → HA gain → sound → protein
const { lang = 'en' } = Astro.props;

const timeline = [
  { time: 'Day 0.5', protein: '3,087', pct: 20.6, loss: '38.5', haGain: '17.7', status: 'Early improvement', barPct: 10 },
  { time: 'Day 1', protein: '16,198', pct: 108.0, loss: '7.9', haGain: '3.7', status: 'Full therapeutic', barPct: 54 },
  { time: 'Day 3', protein: '24,092', pct: 160.6, loss: '4.0', haGain: '0.0', status: 'HA gain → 0', barPct: 80 },
  { time: 'Week 1', protein: '26,511', pct: 176.7, loss: '3.3', haGain: '0.0', status: 'Near equilibrium', barPct: 88 },
  { time: 'Week 2', protein: '27,473', pct: 183.2, loss: '3.1', haGain: '0.0', status: 'Equilibrium', barPct: 92 },
  { time: 'Month 3', protein: '27,617', pct: 184.1, loss: '3.1', haGain: '0.0', status: 'Stable', barPct: 92 },
];

const stressTests = [
  { name: 'HA lost 14 days', sixX: '-0.3%', nineX: '-26.8%', verdict: '9x responds to silence. 6x doesn\'t.' },
  { name: 'Hospital 30 days (25 dB)', sixX: '-1.0%', nineX: '-49.4%', verdict: 'One half-life. Full recovery in 2 weeks.' },
  { name: 'Min dB for therapy (no HA)', sixX: '0 dB', nineX: '45 dB', verdict: '9x needs real sound. 6x is constitutive.' },
];
---

<div class="bg-white/[0.02] border border-purple-500/20 rounded-lg p-5 mb-6">
  <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
    <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400">Closed-Loop Model: True Self-Dosing</h3>
    <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] rounded bg-purple-500/20 text-purple-400 font-semibold">NEW</span>
  </div>
  <p class="text-xs text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Previous ODE models used fixed sound profiles. This model closes the feedback loop:
    protein accumulates → hearing improves → audiologist reduces hearing aid gain →
    less MET activation → less STRC production → equilibrium.
    The hearing aid becomes a true dosing device.
  </p>

  <!-- Feedback loop diagram -->
  <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 text-[9px] font-mono mb-5 flex-wrap">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded bg-cyan-500/10 border border-cyan-500/20 text-cyan-400">Sound</span>
    <span class="text-neutral-600">→</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/20 text-green-400">Ca²⁺</span>
    <span class="text-neutral-600">→</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded bg-yellow-500/10 border border-yellow-500/20 text-yellow-400">NFAT</span>
    <span class="text-neutral-600">→</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded bg-purple-500/10 border border-purple-500/20 text-purple-400">Stereocilin</span>
    <span class="text-neutral-600">→</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-500/20 text-blue-400">Hearing ↑</span>
    <span class="text-neutral-600">→</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded bg-red-500/10 border border-red-500/20 text-red-400">HA gain ↓</span>
    <span class="text-neutral-600">→</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded bg-cyan-500/10 border border-cyan-500/20 text-cyan-400">Sound ↓</span>
  </div>

  <!-- Clinical timeline -->
  <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-neutral-300 mb-2">Clinical Timeline (9xNFAT-weak, 50 dB ambient)</h4>
  <div class="space-y-1 mb-4">
    {timeline.map(t => (
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[10px]">
        <span class="text-neutral-500 w-16 shrink-0 text-right">{t.time}</span>
        <div class="flex-1 h-2 bg-white/5 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
          <div class="h-full bg-purple-500/50 rounded-full" style={`width:${t.barPct}%`}></div>
        </div>
        <span class="text-purple-400 font-mono w-12 text-right shrink-0">{t.pct.toFixed(0)}%</span>
        <span class="text-neutral-600 w-20 shrink-0 hidden sm:block text-right">loss: {t.loss} dB</span>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <div class="bg-green-500/5 border border-green-500/15 rounded p-3 mb-4">
    <p class="text-[10px] text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
      <strong class="text-green-400">Day 3:</strong> Hearing improves enough that HA adds zero gain.
      System reaches equilibrium at <strong class="text-green-400">27,617 molecules</strong> (184% of target),
      <strong class="text-green-400">3.1 dB</strong> residual hearing loss, maintained by ambient sound alone.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Stress tests -->
<div class="bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/5 rounded-lg p-5 mb-6">
  <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Stress Tests: 6xNFAT-strong vs 9xNFAT-weak</h3>
  <p class="text-xs text-neutral-400 mb-3">
    The promoters behave identically under normal conditions. The difference appears when
    sound is removed. This is the test of real self-dosing.
  </p>
  <div class="space-y-2">
    {stressTests.map(st => (
      <div class="bg-white/[0.02] rounded p-3">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[11px] mb-1">
          <span class="text-neutral-200 font-medium flex-1">{st.name}</span>
          <span class="text-neutral-500 font-mono w-20 text-right">6x: {st.sixX}</span>
          <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono w-20 text-right">9x: {st.nineX}</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[10px] text-neutral-500">{st.verdict}</p>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <div class="mt-3 bg-white/[0.03] rounded p-3 text-[10px] text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
    <strong class="text-neutral-300">Built-in resilience:</strong> Stereocilin t½ = 30 days. Even 2 weeks without
    any sound loses only ~27% of protein. Recovery: 98% within 2 weeks of HA restoration.
    Self-dosing is a slow process (weeks), not fast (hours). The long protein half-life
    buffers against daily sound fluctuations.
  </div>
</div>
